text: Fuchiba is a genus of African araneomorph spiders in the family Trachelidae, first described by C. R. Haddad & R. Lyle in 2008. ==Species== it contains six species: *Fuchiba aquilonia Haddad & Lyle, 2008 (type) – Botswana, Mozambique, South Africa *Fuchiba capensis Haddad & Lyle, 2008 – South Africa *Fuchiba montana Haddad & Lyle, 2008 – South Africa, Lesotho *Fuchiba similis Haddad & Lyle, 2008 – South Africa *Fuchiba tortilis Haddad & Lyle, 2008 – South Africa *Fuchiba venteri Haddad & Lyle, 2008 – South Africa ==References== Category:Araneomorphae genera Category:Araneomorphae stubs Category:Trachelidae
title: Fuchiba
